      • getInstance

        @NonNull
public static TallyGo getInstance(@NonNull
                                           android.content.Context context,
                                           @Nullable
                                           java.lang.String accessToken)
        Returns the TallyGo SDK instance that may not yet be initialized. It is a good idea to either use a TallyGo class that initializes the SDK and provides blocking UI or to make a call to initializeFromMetaData(Context, InitializeCallback) when your application will use TallyGo for the first time. If the SDK has been initialized before, this will return synchronously with an initialized SDK.
        Returns:
        the singleton instance of the TallyGo SDK

      • isInitialized

        public static boolean isInitialized()
        Checks to see if the TallyGo SDK has successfully initialized. This must be true to use the SDK. It is possible for an instance to exist that is not initialized. It is acceptable to make additional calls to initialize if the SDK did not initialize properly.
        Returns:
        whether or not the SDK is initialized and available for use

      • initializeFromMetaData

        public static void initializeFromMetaData(@NonNull
                                          android.content.Context context,
                                          @Nullable
                                          TallyGo.InitializeCallback callback)
        Used to initialize the SDK from meta data supplied in the AndroidManifest.xml Meta data must be supplied under the application tag in the AndroidManifest.xml using the META_DATA_ACCESS_TOKEN_KEY to identify the access token. It is advised to put the access token inside of strings.xml and reference it in the meta data. Example strings.xml: <string name="tallygo_access_token">YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN</string> Example AndroidManifest.xml: <application> <meta-data android:name="tallygo.ACCESS_TOKEN" android:value="@string/tallygo_access_token"/> </application> An access token can be acquired at https://tallygo.com/signup It is also possible to set an SDK override config name in the AndroidManifest.xml using: <application> <meta-data android:name="tallygo.ACCESS_TOKEN" android:value="@string/tallygo_access_token"/> </application>
        Parameters:
        context - the context that will supply the application context
        callback - the callback that will inform the caller about the status of the initialization

      • initializeFromMetaData

        public static void initializeFromMetaData(@NonNull
                                          android.content.Context context,
                                          @Nullable

        Parameters:

        overrideSdkString - the sdk config string to use
        accessToken - the access token to use
        callback - the callback to listen to initialization or null if no listener is needed

        public void setClientId(java.lang.String clientId)
